description:
HELLMANNâ€™S DRESSINGS NOW HAVE 3 NEW VEGAN FLAVORS: Smoked Chili, Charred Tomato & Capers, and Miso Ponzu. 
\
My personal favorite is the Smoked Chili and I love putting it in my roasted veggies to go with my Sisig Grain Bowl (recipe below) Or if you want something more improvised. Whip up a pasta dish really quick with the Charred Tomato & Capers. It canâ€™t get any easier to use it as topping or dipping, so I topped my vegan sashimi with the Miso Ponzu dressing. QUICK TRIVIA - These vegan flavors have been formulated in the Philippines! Hooray for more vegan products in the Philippines! 

ROASTED VEGGIES: 
1/2 cup chopped carrots 
1/2 cup chopped potatoes 
1/2 cup chopped sweet potatoes or squash 
few broccoli florets (optional) 
1/4 cup chopped red bell pepper 
drizzle of olive oil 
few pinches sea salt 
few pinches dried rosemary (or preferred dried spices) 

Mix everything in a bowl and roast in an oven or air fryer at 375F for 30 minutes or until the potatoes are nicely charred. 

SISIG GRAIN BOWL 
Cooking oil 
4 cloves garlic, minced 
1 medium onion, minced 
1/2 cup chopped mushrooms 
1/2 cup garbanzo beans 
4 tablespoons soy sauce 
2 tablespoons coconut vinegar 
1 tablespoon raw sugar 
1 sliced chili pepper 
salt and pepper to taste 

1. Pour oil in a medium pan and once hot add the garlic and onions. Cook until the onions have softened. 
2. Add the mushrooms and garbanzo beans. Mix well. 
3. Mix in the soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, chili pepper, salt and pepper. Adjust seasoning
